Q.23 Create a form.jsp which accepts username & password and submits the data to other jsp page which checks if the password is valid then sends the response to 
     success.jsp page which displays a message as "Valid Login" otherwise sends the response to failure.jsp which displays message "Invalid login" .Use JSTL tag to compare.
     
=

//form.jsp

<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1"
    pageEncoding="ISO-8859-1"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Insert title here</title>
</head>
<body>
<form action="jsp23.jsp" method="get">
ENTER USERNAME : <input type="text" name="us">
ENTER PASWORD : <input type="text" name="pass">
<input type="submit" value="Enter">
</form>
</body>
</html>

//jsp - 1

